  <!-- ================= ABOUT SRILA PRABHUPADA ================= -->
  <section class="bg-white py-12 sm:py-16 lg:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
      <!-- Heading -->
      <div class="text-center mb-10 lg:mb-12">
        <h2
          class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl lg:text-4xl text-primary-hover font-bold"
        >
          About Srila Prabhupada
        </h2>

        <!-- Correct Border -->
        <span
          class="block mx-auto mt-4 w-16 sm:w-20 md:w-24 lg:w-32 h-1 bg-primary rounded"
        ></span>
      </div>

      <!-- Content -->
      <div
        class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 sm:gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center"
      >
        <!-- Left Image -->
        <div class="flex justify-center">
          <img
            src="../assets/images/About-Srila-Prabhupada.png"
            alt="Srila Prabhupada"
            class="max-w-full h-auto object-contain"
          />
        </div>

        <!-- Right Text -->
        <div
          class="text-primary-hover text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed font-medium"
        >
          <p>
            Srila Prabhupada, born Abhay Charan Bhaktivedanta Swami in 1896, was
            a spiritual leader and the founder of the International Society for
            Krishna Consciousness (ISKCON). He dedicated his life to spreading
            the teachings of Lord Krishna worldwide, writing over 147 books and
            establishing temples across six continents. At the age of 69, he
            arrived in New York City with little money but immense
            determination. Through his teachings, books, and guidance, he
            inspired thousands and established ISKCON as a global spiritual
            movement.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

